ic_en", "text": "gem:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and also applied (as in the T, M, Mgh, Msb, and K, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tiborN", "text_ar": "تِبْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.,) to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "native ore:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any stone from which is extracted,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "elicited, anything by which one may profit:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) n. un. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) [pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jawaAhiru", "text_ar": "جَوَاهِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] it is of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawoEalu", "text_ar": "فَوْعَلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) and is from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljahoru", "text_ar": "الجَهْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying a thing's “ becoming exceedingly plain to be perceived by the sense of sight: ” (Er-Rághib, TA:) or it is of Persian origin, (TA,) arabicized, (S, TA,) [from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Gawoharo", "text_ar": "گَوْهَرْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] accord. to most persons. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jawoharu sayofK", "text_ar": "جَوْهَرُ سَيْفٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The diversified wavy marks, streaks,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grain, of a sword;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "firinodN", "text_ar": "فِرِنْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T and K voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "firinodN", "text_ar": "فِرِنْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jawoharu $aYo'K", "text_ar": "جَوْهَرُ شَىْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The essence of a thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that whereby a thing is what it is; the substance of a thing: the constituent of a thing; the material part thereof;] that upon which the natural con-"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 476}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stitution of a thing is as it were based;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of which its natural constitution is made to be;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or, as IbrD thinks to be meant in the K,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the collective parts and materials of a thing, of which its natural constitution is moulded;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] expl. by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maAwuDiEato", "text_ar": "مَاوُضِعَتْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayohi jibil~atuhu", "text_ar": "عَلَيْهِ جِبِلَّتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) or, as in some Lexicons, [as the JK and the Msb,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA xuliqato Ealayohi jibil~atuhu", "text_ar": "مَا خُلِقَتْ عَلَيْهِ جِبِلَّتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is virtually the same]: (TA:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljawoharu", "text_ar": "الجَوْهَرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al*~aAtu", "text_ar": "الذَّاتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmaAhiy~apu", "text_ar": "المَاهِيَّةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaqiyqapu", "text_ar": "الحَقِيقَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are all syn. terms; and the first has other significations; but in the classical language it signifies"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aSolu", "text_ar": "الاَصْلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSolu Almurak~abaAti", "text_ar": "اَصْلُ المُرَكَّبَاتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the original of compound things"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and not what subsists by itself. (Kull.) ―         -b4-  [Hence,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljawoharu Alfarodu", "text_ar": "الجَوْهَرُ الفَرْدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The indivisible atom."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b5-  In the conventional language of scholastic theology,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jawoharN", "text_ar": "جَوْهَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Substance, as opposed to accident;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in which sense, some assert the word to be so much used as to be, in this sense, conventionally regarded as proper. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jahowarN", "text_ar": "جَهْوَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "K", "S", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n6783", "headword_ar": "جَوْهَرٌ", "root": "jwhr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jhr", "text_ar": "جهر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}